                <p n="1"><pb ed="L642 L633" n="1v"/>ndah nihan varahakna mami rumuhun ri saṅ sevaka dharma katkan kita rumәṅәkna 
                    <app><lem wit="#L633">kavivekan</lem><rdg wit="#L642">kaviven</rdg></app> saṅ hyaṅ dharma, mvaṅ 
                    <app><lem type="emn">kabyavasthānikaṅ</lem><rdg wit="#L642">kabyaṁvasṭanikaṁ</rdg><rdg wit="#L633">kabyavas·tanika</rdg></app> saṅ hyaṅ ajñāna, hana 
                    <app><lem type="norm">trikāyamaṇḍala</lem><rdg wit="#L633">trikaya man·dala</rdg><rdg wit="#L642">trakayamandala</rdg></app> pariśuddha, 
                    <app><lem wit="#L642">ṅa</lem><rdg wit="#L633">ṅaranya</rdg></app>, inujarakәn saṅ pandita ri saṅ sevaka dharma, ya pantahan 
                    <app><lem type="emn">kveki</lem><rdg wit="#L642">kvaki</rdg><rdg wit="#L633">kvakiṅ</rdg></app> ulah śabda lavan ambәk, 
                    <app><lem type="emn">yan kva</lem><rdg wit="#L642">yekva</rdg><rdg wit="#L633">yekvaṁ</rdg></app> hana 
                    <app><lem type="norm">ma<pb ed="L633" n="2r"/>līna</lem><rdg wit="#L642">malina:</rdg><rdg wit="#L633">maṁline</rdg></app> ri 
                    <app><lem type="emn">hr̥dayanta</lem><rdg wit="#L642">pr̥ḍayanta</rdg><rdg wit="#L633">prǝdayan·ta</rdg></app>, ya teka 
                    <app><lem wit="#L642">prah</lem><rdg wit="#L633">prǝh</rdg></app> pәgәṅәn rakṣa pahayu juga ya, apan 
                    <app><lem type="emn">hetuniṅ</lem><rdg wit="#L642">hentaniṁ</rdg><rdg wit="#L633">hentuniṁ</rdg></app> 
                    <app><lem wit="#L633">manәmvakәn</lem><rdg wit="#L642">manimvakәn</rdg></app> śukhadukha halahayu,</p>
                
                <p n="2">yan pinahala ulahta, śabdata, 
                    <app><lem type="norm">ambәkta</lem><rdg wit="#L633">Ambhǝkta</rdg><rdg wit="#L642">Ambhakta</rdg></app>, niyata 
                    <app><lem type="norm">kapaṅguhnikaṅ</lem><rdg wit="#L633 #L642">kapaguḥnikaṁ</rdg></app> hala denta yan maṅkana, yan pinahayu ulahta, <pb ed="#L642" n="2r"/>
 śabdata, ambәkta, avas kapaṅguhnikaṅ hayuta yan maṅkana, mataṅyan hana paribhāṣa kumva ṅ 
                    <app><lem wit="#L642">madyus-dyus</lem><rdg wit="#L633">ḍyas·ḍyas·</rdg></app> vvay tinәmunya 
                    <app><lem type="emn">kasvabhāvaniṅ</lem><rdg wit="#L642 #L633">kasvambhavaniṁ</rdg></app> janma, hala tumәmu halanya, hayu tumәmu hayunya, maṅkana 
                    <app><lem wit="#L642">lvirniṅ</lem><rdg wit="#L633">lvarniṁ</rdg></app> janma,</p>
               
                <p n="3">ndya ḍr̥ṣṭānta, i riki dadyanya, hala deniṅ halanya, hayu deniṅ hayunya, nihan upadyanta hana ya maṇik anargha, ṅa, tan 
                    <app><lem wit="#L642">kinavruhan</lem><rdg wit="#L633">kinavraḥhan·</rdg></app> mulyanya, tan paprameya ri rahayu, kaliṅanya ikaṅ maṇik anargha, lavan maṇik 
                    <app><lem type="emn">sarveṣṭa</lem><rdg wit="#L642">ṣavesṭaṭā</rdg><rdg wit="#L633">ṣavesṭa</rdg></app>, yvagya karikāpusәn 
                    <app><lem type="emn">kari</lem><rdg wit="#L642 #L633">ta ri</rdg></app> gaṅsa, tambaga lavan timah, aparan ta yvagyanika, niyatār <pb ed="#L642" n="2v"/> mijil śrīnika lavan dhanuhnika, maṅka pva 
                    <app><lem wit="#L642">yvagya</lem><rdg wit="#L633">gyapa</rdg></app> paṅapusan ta irikaṅ maṇik anargha, paṅikәtan ta irikaṅ maṇik 
                    <app><lem type="emn">sarveṣṭa</lem><rdg wit="#L642 #L633">ṣavesṭa</rdg></app>, 
                </p>
                
                <p n="4">nihan liṅnira ri saṅ hyaṅ śāstra</p>
                <p n="5"><foreign>lpas ca vuṁkunuṁ ceva, aḍika udika tatte tatur tathya tuṅgәṁ, ta deva nigaḍyate </foreign></p>
                <p n="6">apan sinaṅguh rambut lәpas, ṅa, vulu pasagi, ṅa, hana uḍika, hana tater, hana sorasa, ṅa, ika ta kabaih yvagya karika paṅapusan ta irikaṅ maṇik anargha, paṅikәtan ta irikaṅ maṇik 
                    <app><lem type="emn">sarveṣṭa</lem><rdg wit="#L642 #L633">ṣavesṭa</rdg></app>, taham pih yāpusәn ta ri gaṅsa tambaga lavan timah, aparan ta yvagyanika, paṅapusan ta irikaṅ maṇik anargha, paṅikә<pb ed="#L642" n="3r"/>tan ta irikaṅ maṇik sarveṣṭa, nahan liṅnya ri saṅ hyaṅ śāstra, <foreign>lpәs ca vuṁkunuṁ 
                        <app><lem wit="#L633">ceva</lem><rdg wit="#L642">cova</rdg></app>, Aḍi Ikaṁ, Uḍi Ika:, tate:r tatur tatya tuṅgәṅ nu yvagyanika</foreign>
                    <!-- THIS PARAGRAPH IS STILL CONFUSING -->
